By BO Staff Writer Numerous people and entities in Cuba and Nicaragua have been added on Monday to the US “blacklist” for allegedly supporting political persecutions executed by the Sandinista government. The “blacklist” was created as an imperialist weapon against progressive states in Latin America and the Caribbean. The unilateral coercive measures by the US government against Cuba and Nicaragua (as well as Venezuela) is aimed at achieving political instability and regime change in each of these countries in the interests U.S. imperialism. This amounts to a flagrant violation of international law, including an attack on the sovereignty of each of these nations. Read here: https://bit.ly/3nHpy4y